%S A395776 1,1,2,2,6,2,8,4,6,6,12,4,12,8,12,8,18,6,20,12,16,12,23,8,30,12,18,16,
%T A395776 28,12,30,16,24,18,48,12,38,20,24,24,40,16,44,24,36,23,46,16,56,30,36,
%U A395776 24,54,18,72,32,40,28,58,24,62,30,48,32,72,24,68,36,46,48
%N A395776 The twisted Euler phi-function for the Dirichlet character kronecker(-23,.) mod 23.
%C A395776 We have h(-23*n^2), the class number of the order of Z[(1+sqrt(-23))/2] with discriminant -23*n^2, is equal to 3*a(n).
%C A395776 In general, let d < 0 be a fundamental discriminant and n be a positive integer such that d*n^2 < -4, then h(d*n^2) = L(0,kronecker(d,.)) * n * Product_{p|n, p prime} (1 - kronecker(d,p)/p). This is a combination of Theorem 7.24 in "Primes of the form x^2+ny^2" by Cox and the Dirichlet class number formula. Here L(0,kronecker(-23,.)) = 3.
%D A395776 D. A. Cox, Primes of the form x^2+ny^2, Wiley, New York, 1989, p. 146.
%F A395776 Multiplicative with a(23^e) = 23^e, a(p^e) = p^(e-1)*(p-1) if p == 1, 2, 3, 4, 6, 8, 9, 12, 13, 16, 18 (mod 23) and a(p^e) = p^(e-1)*(p+1) if p == 5, 7, 10, 11, 14, 15, 17, 19, 20, 21, 22 (mod 23).
%e A395776 Given L(0,kronecker(-23,.)) = 3, we have: h(-23*1^2) = 3*a(1) = 3, h(-23*2^2) = 3*a(2) = 3, h(-23*3^2) = 3*a(3) = 6, h(-23*4^2) = 3*a(4) = 6, ...
%o A395776 (PARI) a(n,{d=-23}) = my(f=factor(n)[,1]~, w=#f); n * prod(i=1, w, 1 - kronecker(d,f[i])/f[i])
%Y A395776 A011586 is the corresponding Dirichlet character.
%Y A395776 Cf. for fundamental discriminants -3..-24: A227128, A395768, A395771, A395769, A395772, A395773, A395774, A395775, this sequence, A395777.
%K A395776 nonn,easy,mult,new
%O A395776 1,3
